    <h2>2013 Jordan Nagler Memorial Scholarship Recipient</h2>
    <div class="rtImg"><img src="images/scholarship/2013scholarship.jpg" width="200" height="150"  alt=""/></div>
    <p>ISE is pleased to announce that the recipient of the Jordan Nagler Scholarship for 2013-2014 is Luka Medzmariashvili of Republic of Georgia. In selecting the scholarship recipient, ISE looks for a student who is well rounded – not just having excellent grades, but also being interested and involved in a variety of activities.</p> 

<p>Luka is grateful that ISE gave him such a great opportunity to study in the USA.  Luke loves his home country but he always wanted to go to make friends and learn about American traditions.  He never imagined he would get the opportunity.</p>

<p>“. . . for me it would be the most amazing chance in my life.”</p>

<div class="ltImg"><img src="images/scholarship/2013scholarship_2.jpg" width="200" height="150"  alt=""/></div><p>Learning and improving his English skills are the main reasons why he came here.  When he got here, he adjusted easily by making friends.  He loves his host family in West Richland, WA.  Luka says it’s very beautiful and is lucky to have a host mom that is such a great cook.  His host father brings him to the gym where they get to spend a lot of time together.  Luka shares a lot of interest with his host brother.</p>

<p>“William, my host brother is very smart person, he's the same age as me and we have many common interests.”</p>

<p>Luka attends Hanford high school.  He enjoys his school and the friends he’s making.  He studies very hard on his English language skills.  He appreciates his access to advanced technology and research.  Luka has been able to take advantage of the experiences that go along with lesson plans.</p> 

<p>“Studying in the United States doesn’t just give me tangible degrees and certificates, my experience says something about who I am.”</p>

<p>He does say living in another country where his language isn’t spoken is challenging.  Luka overcomes it with courage and a positive attitude.</p> 

<p>The scholarship is in honor of Jordan Nagler who was the Executive Director of International Student Exchange from 2003 until his passing in October of 2008. The criteria for this scholarship selection is academic excellence and a diligent work ethic. These traits exemplify the work and life of Jordan Nagler, and ISE is proud to recognize and reward those characteristics in Luka.</p>

<p>The young people chosen for this scholarship work hard to be excellent students and have a full life. These traits exemplify the work and life of Jordan Nagler, and ISE is proud to recognize and reward those characteristics through this scholarship.</p><!--2013 Recipient---></div>

